  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor / Procurement Specialist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description & Responsibilities:</strong><br />\nThe Quantity Surveyor with procurement experience will be responsible for\nmanaging project costs, procurement, and contracts from inception to\ncompletion. This role requires <strong>liaising and coordinating with contractors,\nvendors, and suppliers</strong>, as well as the <strong>possibility of onsite work</strong> to\nsupport project execution. Key responsibilities include:</p><ul><li>Prepare detailed <strong>cost analyses</strong> based on architectural drawings, engineering\nestimates, and required materials.</li><li><strong>Source vendors and contractors</strong>, obtain quotations, and evaluate tender\nsubmissions.</li><li><strong>Negotiate contracts</strong>, including terms, conditions, and pricing, ensuring\nexecution aligns with agreements.</li><li>Prepare and manage <strong>tender and contract documents</strong>, including bills of\nquantities.</li><li>Monitor and control project expenditures, including measurement and valuation of\nvariations, interim payments, and final accounts.</li><li><strong>Manage procurement activities</strong>: prepare purchase orders, liaise with\nsubcontractors, suppliers, logistics partners, and warehouse for smooth\nend-to-end supply chain flow.</li><li><strong>Coordinate with contractors and vendors</strong>, ensuring timely delivery, quality, and\nadherence to project requirements.</li><li>May be required to work <strong>onsite (less often)</strong> for project coordination, inspections, or\ncontractor supervision.</li><li>Maintain <strong>accurate project records and documentation</strong>.</li><li>Communicate regularly with project staff, consultants, subcontractors, suppliers, and\nChina-based counterparts.</li><li>Perform any other ad hoc assignments as directed by management.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Bachelor’s degree in <strong>Quantity Surveying, Civil, or Mechanical\nEngineering</strong>.</li><li>Minimum <strong>5 years relevant experience</strong> in construction, with strong knowledge\nof contracts, procurement, and material costing.</li><li><strong>Fluent in Mandarin</strong> to liaise effectively with China-based teams.</li><li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills.</li><li>Strong ability to <strong>prioritize tasks and manage deadlines</strong>.</li><li>Proficient in cost estimation, tender evaluation, and budget control.</li><li>Highly <strong>organized, independent, and self-motivated</strong>, with strong\nrecord-keeping skills.</li><li>Able to work <strong>under pressure</strong>, both in the office and <strong>onsite</strong>, and\ncollaboratively in a team environment.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
